<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1699,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[369,442,1772,1796]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: North, Central-West, and Southeast regions (PA, MT, RO, MG) (
<bibRefCitation author="Drake &amp; Harris" box="[1187,1431,1772,1796]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref36495" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1930) Notes on some South American Gerridae (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 19, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1930">Drake &amp; Harris 1930</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuitert" box="[151,296,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Kuitert" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="113 - 143" refId="ref39042" refString="Kuitert, L. C. (1942) Gerrinae in the University of Kansas Collections. University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 28, 113 - 143." type="journal article" year="1942">Kuitert 1942</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[308,459,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="94 - 138" refId="ref40669" refString="Nieser, N. (1970 c) Gerridae of the Suriname and the Amazon with additional records of other neotropical species. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 12, 94 - 138." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="c">Nieser 1970c</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sampaio &amp; Py-Daniel" box="[471,784,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Sampaio" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="83 - 94" refId="ref42917" refString="Sampaio, R. T. M. &amp; Py-Daniel, V. (1993) A subfamilia Gerrinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) na Bacia Hidrografica do Rio Trombetas, Para, Brazil. Acta Amazonica, 23, 83 - 94." type="journal article" year="1993">Sampaio &amp; Py-Daniel 1993</bibRefCitation>
; Nieser &amp; Melo 1997).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1699,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Comments: Described from “Chapada, 
<collectingCountry box="[645,718,1844,1868]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
,” but in this case 
<bibRefCitation author="Drake and Harris" box="[922,1201,1844,1868]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref36495" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1930) Notes on some South American Gerridae (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 19, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1930">Drake and Harris (1930)</bibRefCitation>
provided the collector’s name “H. H. Smith.” See discussion under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1930" box="[692,869,1880,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Limnogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="profugus" subGenus="Limnogonus">
<emphasis box="[692,715,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[731,754,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[770,869,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">profugus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,611,151,176]" box="[151,611,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1913" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1913" box="[151,483,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Neogerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,483,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,264,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Neogerris</emphasis>
Matsumura, 1913
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(6 species)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,223,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Comments: Variations in pronotal length caused specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(White, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[890,1242,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Neogerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus">
<emphasis box="[890,1069,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Neogerris lotus</emphasis>
(White, 1879)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(White, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Neogerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubricus">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">N. lubricus</emphasis>
(White, 1879)
</taxonomicName>
to be wrongly identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Drake &amp; Harris, 1934)" baseAuthorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[628,1010,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Neogerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celeris">
<emphasis box="[628,736,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">N. celeris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Drake &amp; Harris" box="[752,1002,260,284]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="179 - 241" refId="ref36685" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1934) The Gerrinae of the Western Hemisphere (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 23, 179 - 241." type="journal article" year="1934">Drake &amp; Harris, 1934</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the literature. Because of this fact, Nieser (1994) restricted the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[779,886,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Neogerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celeris">
<emphasis box="[779,886,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">N. celeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to its type-locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1130,1235,296,320]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, and records from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,332,356]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
are not considered.
</paragraph>
